MIUI ROM Database 2023 | Advanced Search
  • FULLROM TGZ or Fastboot ROM use with Fastboot mode (Volume– and Power buttons).
    Requires a Windows PC/Laptop and MiFlash tool. You need to unlock your phone.
    See more detail at https://c.mi.com/oc/miuidownload/detail?guide=2
  • ROM ZIP or Recovery ROM use with Recovery mode (Volume+ and Power buttons).
    Upgrade by click the About phone > System update > ... > Choose Update Package
    To show that hidden menu, click on the MIUI logo 7 times.
    See more detail at https://c.mi.com/oc/miuidownload/detail?guide=1
  • OTA ZIP ROM is an Increment Recovery ROM used for upgrading from your current ROM.
    Since the file is small, good for upgrade by 4G/5G connection (Over-The-Air).
  • Stable Beta Recovery ROM is the final public testing and pushes updates to the smallest
    number of users. You should delay a month before updating to the newest version.
    When the Fastboot ROM is released, it will mark as a Stable Recovery ROM.
  • Some devices have the wrong region.
  • Date is taken from the Last-Modified header.
Tip: Sort multiple columns by holding down the Ctrl key and clicking a column header.
